Barclays, LSE, Pernod, Porsche, Veolia: European Equity Preview

-- B y   N i k o l a j   G a m m e l t o f t
-- 
2011-06-16T04:00:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-15/barclays-lse-pernod-porsche-veolia-european-equity-preview.html
The following companies’ shares may
be active in European trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses.  The Stoxx Europe 600 Index fell 1.1 to 267.95. The Stoxx 50
Index slumped 1 percent to 2,510.15. The Euro Stoxx 50 Index, a
benchmark for nations using the euro, decreased 1.7 percent to
2,731.50.  Air Liquide SA (AI)  : The world’s biggest producer of
industrial gases won a contract to supply hydrogen to two Valero
Energy Corp. refineries in  Texas . The shares fell 1.7 percent to
92.78 euros.  Barclays Plc (BARC)  : The U.K.’s second-largest bank said
it intends to generate additional revenue of as much as 6.4
billion pounds ($10.4 billion) by 2013. The lender will budget
operating expenses of 16.8 billion pounds by 2013, saving at
least 1 billion pounds in costs, it said in slides based on a
presentation to analysts. The shares retreated 2.7 percent to
257.4 pence.  Eurasian Natural Resources Corp. (ENRC LN): Standard &
Poor’s Ratings Services placed the metal producer’s BB+ long-
term corporate credit rating on CreditWatch with negative
implications, citing “concerns about what we view as major
governance issues,” S&P said in a statement. The shares dropped
2.3 percent to 744 pence.  France Telecom SA (FTE)  : The telecommunications group
said it closed a 670 million-euro issue of bonds maturing in
2019 and 2021, to take advantage of the decrease in  interest
rates  since mid-April. The shares fell 2.1 percent to 14.28
euros.  Glencore International Plc (GLEN LN): The largest listed
commodity trader has been barred by the U.K. Takeover Panel from
bidding for Eurasian Natural Resources Corp. for six months
after stating it’s not studying an offer. The shares fell 5.4
percent to 473 pence.  London Stock Exchange Group Plc (LSE)  : TMX Group Inc.
Chief Executive Officer Thomas Kloet said critics are wrong to
think the exchange operator’s purchase by London Stock Exchange
Group puts the company’s Montreal derivatives bourse in
jeopardy. LSE’s stock retreated 1.4 percent to 955 pence.  Pernod Ricard SA (RI FP): The French drinks group said it
would pay an interim cash dividend of 67 cents on July 6. The
shares fell 0.9 percent to 66.74.  Porsche Automobil Holding SE (PAH3)  (PAH3 GY): The carmaker sold
$518 million of bonds backed by automobile loans, according to a
person familiar with the transaction. The shares fell 0.1
percent to 47.12 euros.  ProSiebenSat.1 Media AG (PSM)  : The owners of  Germany ’s
biggest broadcaster are asking lenders to change the terms on
loans so that a share sale won’t trigger a debt repayment,
 Reuters  reported, citing unidentified people familiar with the
matter. The shares fell 2.6 percent to 18.70 euros.  Veolia Environnement SA (VIE)  : The French utility
company said it would pay 63.7% of its dividend in shares,
resulting in a capital increase of 382.3 million euros, with
20.5 million new shares to begin trading on June 17. The shares
fell 2 percent to 19.65 euros.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nikolaj Gammeltoft in New York at 
